caption: We came to this spot for dinner. This spot was recommended to us by a friend.  Well, we were not disappointed. The staff were extremely nice and we felt good. The food was just great. We had a great time and we will visit this place again. we highly recommend this place.
Love this place! I have lunch every time I go to the city.
This spot clearly knows how to serve their clients. Constantly with a super nice attitude. The food is affordably priced, always yummy and neat.
SUCH AN AMAZING PLACE!!!
Good :-)
It was OK. Miso was tasty but cold, all ingredients are not integrated in one flavor soup.

Great spot to grab some tasty ramen. I have tried to go with friends late on a Saturday night before and been turned away but luckily we made it there by 10:40pm and they sat us. I'm not a big nori fan. So, I was super pleased to find it doesn't come standard accompaniment. Look forward to eating here again.

A very interesting and tasty bowl of ramen. The sukiyaki beef in ramen is not something Ive ever had before. Delicious to have the pops of sweetness from the beef and corn. Had the amami, chicken and beef was delicious. The chashu was a bit tough and dry.
Chashu was tough. Good, but slow service.
Great ramen and spam musubi. Staff was really friendly too.
Taste good large portions
Just what I wanted. Tender meats, tasty broth, and just the right amount of heat. I got the Amami with the kontostu with medium spice. I'll be back!!
For an inexpensive hot meal,  the House Ramen and Tonkotsu spicy is delicious.

It's not the highest quality ramen you'll get in SF but a great local option and a decent price. Be warned, space (seating) is very limited in here so you'll either be sitting right next to another customer or facing a mirrored wall with a …
Great Ramen! Even my husband liked it, and he’s usually not into this type of food. Staff was very friendly. I would go here again and again and again.
Very packed place and the owner helped seat people who ordered. Food was tasty and spicy if you like.
The ramen is delicious, will come back on my next trip to San Francisco.

Good spot for quick decent ramen with a relatively short wait. There are a number of meat options outside of the classic pork belly. You can also opt for spicy or not.  Relatively limited seating so if you're looking to sit down I'd probably get there on the earlier side.
Incredible value for great ramen. Spicy was a good idea. $3 beer draughts, too! 100% will be back.
Great, fresh ramen. Hole in the wall spot, seating is pretty cozy and limited

So, I'm not a "Amami foodie" BUT DAM IT'S GOOD! I jus needed something good for my lunch break, something to take my mind off work. I ordered the Chicken ramen with Tonkotsu broth (mild) it was delicious and perfect, thank you Abby!
Nice store, great value for money, good service and DELICIOUS ramen and pork gyoza.
Miso Spicy Ramen was delicious, and very affordable. Yum!
Its ok ramen... beef cut was not great. Service is nice and personable. Ambiance could be better, good price/performance
One od the most tasty ramen I have ever tried! ❤
My fav place for delicious Ramen. Staff is always super even when they have a full house. The service was very sociable and kind.

Ordered Tonkotsu Amami ramen spicy and sapporo...and it was excellent...bento b too....we recommend...100%...thanks.

Very good authentic ramen! The staff is a little hands off yet pleasant. Any complaints are heavily outweighed by the food in my opinion.
Delicious!!!!!

Was recommended by a friend. As i ws looking for vegetarian option, i was a bit hesitant at first as most ramen house uses pork broth. Was pleasantly surprised that they've good options for vegetarian. And if you're those who go without garlic/onions, you can tell them so. Overall taste was pretty good
Went back in March & this was the first time I had ramen. Completely fell in love & I crave ramen from this specific place every time! I live in LA and haven’t found a place as good as this one.

Work trip brought me there.  The soup of the spicy miso vegetable ramen was very good, the major disappointment has been the noodles. It tasted of the alkaline water that is often found in chinese noodles that have not been properly washed.  I am glad that I had spicy soup to wash it down, else it would have been difficult to swallow.

I was slightly inebriated when visiting AMAMI and that made it even tastier! I've visited Japan a few times, mostly for skiing the northern island of Hokkaido, and AMAMI is true to what I remember. The bowls were super hot and spicy with …
Nice Ramen in Town, reasonable price. I ordered spicy ramen it is a little bit hot..but yummy.

(Translated by Google) The store name amami ramen is topped with pork, chicken, beef, boiled eggs and vegetables. You can choose between mild and hot spices.  (Original) 店名のamami ramen はチャーシュー、鳥、牛、ゆで卵、野菜のトッピング。スパイスがマイルドとホットが選べる。

Good ramen for decent price. Not a big bowl of noodles as far as quantity. Had the house ramen, the meat lacked flavor but the broth was good and the ingredients such as corn sprouts and scallions and green bean made up for the lack of bigger portion of noodles. Service was good and water is served in small disposal paper cups.
I need more pork free options

Came on a weekday at 1130, when they first open for the day. Def come before 12, before lunch crowd appears, then it's individual seats mostly. Ordered the Amami ramen with Tonkotsu broth. Very tasty and generous amounts of meat (3 types!). …
Best ramen in San Francisco (from a tourist point of view). Fast and cheap, they have so many choices of ramen, I would have been back there again and again
Best fast food place on Japanese ramen establishment. Nice and friendly staff  !!

Really good ramen - but I have to say that I only go to this ramen restaurant in San Francisco - for me the Ramen was good because the ramen I ate in Berlin are similar or less good than this one. I had the Housesoup with the miso base. It was delicious!!!
Yummy. Filling. Would come back again.
Good ramen dish !
Came here because the line at Mensho Tokyo was too long. The ramen was just okay, was missing some deeper flavors like roasted garlic or seaweed.
Just paid $18.80 for the house ramen that was so bad I had to spit it out. Pork tasted rancid.  Their spam masugi was great and the made me an authentic green tea!
I go here pretty frequently, just the normal size ramen is worth the price in my opinion, otherwise the special ones aren't worth the extra few dollars. The ramen is okay and the service is fast.

When in San Francisco, have ramen; at Amami. Simple, fast and wholesome. Close to Union Square yet off the beaten path. Plenty of locals dine there and when locals eat there it's a good enough reason to visit.

Best Ramen I’ve ever had! By far! I took the 3 meat, spicy, creamy. It was amazing. The place itself is very small and Unnoticeable, not many seats either, like a hole in a wall. Luckily, the place we usually go to had a line, so we looked for another ramen and stumbled upon AMAMI. Highly recommended!

My wife and I stumbled upon this place. We were walking by and the smell alone drew us in. I had the spicy Tonkotsu which is the number one on the menu and it was amazing! My wife had the Miso chicken and it was outstanding!  This place is …

Can't say anything about their ramen but I did enjoy their bento box combo C (take out). It's a donburi rice bowl with one good sized piece of the following: chicken karage, vegetable dumpling, a potato croquette, as well as egg and a small seaweed salad over rice equals a great meal for $6.95.
Flavorless.

Yummy fillings with a warm crusty batter. No need to travel to Japan when you have the best taiyaki in Union Square. This little hidden gem was recently opened and I was fortunate enough to discover it. I’m sharing this to all over you friends with sweet tooth.
Taiyaki is one of my all time favorite desserts so I was really excited to discover a new shop dedicated to it. It's not the greatest but they have a variety of flavors
Authentic JP desserts!
